Program: Discovery
Title: Whale-falls - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz4p
Last Broadcast Date: 11 April 2006
Whales that fall to the bottom of the ocean and the effect of this on the ecosystem. When a whale sinks after death its corpse provides a huge bonanza for many animals. Over 400 species inhabit whale falls. Presented by Andrew Luck-Baker.